The paper is about a public image recognition challenge designed for deep learning based on web images without instance-level human annotation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The dataset was crawled from the Internet using queries generated from the ILSVRC 2012 dataset, indicating a possible information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also mentions meta information and transfer learning, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, respectively.
